Cook pasta to desired doneness as directed on package. Drain; cover to keep warm. Meanwhile, heat oil in large nonstick skillet over medium-high heat. Add chicken breast tenders, onion, Cajun seasoning, salt and pepper. Cook 5 to 7 minutes, or until chicken is browned and thoroughly cooked. Add frozen vegetables, Alfredo sauce, and half-n-half. Cook and stir until vegetables are hot. Serve chicken mixture over bow ties.